The paper deals with the translation of alternating parity automata to alternating weak automata, which is a topic in formal languages and automata theory. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the blow-up of the number of states, which is related to the size of universal ordered trees, indicating a possible connection to the cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) sub-category. The paper also mentions algorithms for solving parity games, which suggests a connection to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on automata and games suggests a possible connection to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category.
